`LinearOrder` is too strong here. All you need is a codirected order
Nice catch! Yeah, `IsMin.isBot` already exists under that setting.
What about `IsMin.not_isMax`? Those seem to work under either a directed or a codirected order, is that the correct generality?
Think so yeah
and here a directed order
What changed here? Why do you have to repeat all variables?
The variable `Î²` was accidentally being made explicit for all subsequent lemmas.

You can use `variable (Î²) in` before each lemma where it should be explicit (or use `variable (Î²)`, then `variable {Î²}`). This way it's clear that you reuse TC assumptions from `variable`s, just change `Î²` to explicit.
You can prove `IsBot.not_isMax`, then deduce this using `mt IsTop.isMax`.
Can you put this back to the end of the file? The first two are about `Semilattice...` which is stronger than `PartialOrder`, and I don't see why you need to move the last two?
Yeah, I don't remember why I moved these. I'll move them back.
